There is no generic token-refresh standard. Basically this is something you need to implement as part of your API: you just need to add an endpoint (URL) which returns a new JWT token to the user. This could be something as simple as:

```python
@view_config(route_name='token-refresh', permission='view', renderer='json')
def refresh_token(request):
    token = request.create_jwt_token(request.authenticated_userid)
    return { 'token': token }
```

