The "config parsing" thing might look like some configuration in Crossbar like this (e.g. inside a "component"):

```
subscriptions: [
    {
        "topic": "com.example.",
        "handler": "module.sub.my_function",
        "options": {
            "match": "prefix"
        }
    }
]
```

The thing I *don't* like about that, though, is there's some redundancy with what the code says (i.e. you'd be spelling out "options", "topic" etc in the code as well).

A similar option might be to leverage the decorators better and have them 'mark' the functions with the options etc directly, so that the above config would become *just* the essential information:

```
subscriptions: [
    {
        "handler": "module.sub.my_function"
    }
]
```
(or maybe it's just a list of strings that are function-names). Then the crossbar code would introspect the functions (that were marked with the decorators) to pull out topic, options, etc.

