@KEINOS The <code>-e </code> tells shell not to ignore an escape sequence and to treat it as one. Have you tried double escaping and sending ASCII sequences to the terminal? For example, try running:
<code>echo -e \\x20\\x0A\ playlist</code>

If this produces the desired effect, 'q' [Code 0x71] stops the player and returns to the playlist. In theory, [Code 0x0A] 'Enter' would work in this context as well.

